---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Rustzen"
  description="Terms of service for Zen Clear and Rustzen services."
>
  <main class="legal-page">
    <article class="legal-document">
      <p class="eyebrow">Terms</p>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: June 25, 2026</p>

      <p>
        These terms govern your use of Zen Clear, the Rustzen website, and
        Rustzen Cloud services. By using Zen Clear or purchasing Zen Clear Pro,
        you agree to these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Zen Clear</h2>
      <p>
        Zen Clear helps identify development caches, build outputs, tool state,
        and other local files that may be reclaimable. Cleanup is preview-first:
        the app shows scope and risk before an action runs. The default cleanup
        flow moves recoverable items into Zen Clear Restore Center, not macOS
        Trash or direct permanent deletion. You are responsible for reviewing
        cleanup previews, managing Restore Center contents, and keeping backups
        of important data.
      </p>

      <h2>Zen Clear Pro</h2>
      <p>
        Zen Clear Pro is an annual subscription sold through Creem for
        $10/year and activation on up to three devices. The free version can
        scan, preview cleanup results, configure macOS permissions, and check
        for updates. Pro unlocks cleanup, Restore Center, advanced scan rules,
        custom rules, scheduled scans, and license activation,
        subject to the current product description at checkout.
      </p>

      <h2>License Use</h2>
      <p>
        You may use a valid Zen Clear Pro license for your own devices up to the
        device limit shown at checkout. You may not share, resell, reverse
        engineer, bypass, or abuse license keys, activation services, or paid
        features.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>
        You may not use Zen Clear or Rustzen services for unlawful activity,
        malware, credential theft, unauthorized access, system compromise,
        payment abuse, or attempts to disrupt Rustzen or third-party services.
      </p>

      <h2>Subscriptions And Cancellation</h2>
      <p>
        Subscription billing is handled by Creem. You can cancel future renewal
        through the checkout, subscription management flow, or by contacting
        support. Cancellation stops future renewal but does not automatically
        refund past charges.
      </p>

      <h2>Warranty Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        Zen Clear and Rustzen services are provided as available. We work to
        keep cleanup behavior clear and recoverable, but we do not guarantee
        uninterrupted service, error-free results, or that every file identified
        by the app is safe for your specific workflow.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms can be sent to
        <a href="mailto:support@rustzen.dev">support@rustzen.dev</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
